==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[colorise]]
*[[colourise]] (''British'')
*[[colourize]]

===Etymology===
From ''[[colourise]]'' + spelling reforms (''[[colour]]'' to ''[[color]]'' and ''[[-ise]]'' to ''[[-ize]]'').

===Verb===
{{en-infl-verb|coloriz|ing}}

# {{US}} to add color to
#: ''The child '''colorized''' the drawing.''
#: ''The woman '''colorized''' her hair.''
# {{cattag|US|photography|film|slang}} to convert [[black and white]] media to [[color]] by digital post production, often used in digital photography and in video special effects
#: ''There is a '''colorized''' version of Casablanca.''

====Synonyms====
